{"title_page": "Auletta (band)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Auletta\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = [[Mainz]], Germany\n| genre           = [[Indie Rock]], [[Alternative rock|Alternative]]\n| years_active    = {{Start date|df=yes|2005}}&ndash; present\n| label           = EMI Germany\n| website             = {{URL|auletta.de}} \n| current_members    = Alexander Zwick <br> Martin Kloos <br> Johannes Juschzak <br> Daniel Juschzak \n| past_members    =\n}}\n\n'''Auletta''' is an [[Indie-Rock]] band from [[Mainz]], Germany. The band named itself after the town [[Auletta]] in Italy, where they went on holiday in 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.laut.de/wortlaut/artists/a/auletta/biographie/index.htm|title=Auletta Biography|accessdate=17 August 2009|publisher=Laut.de|language=German}}</ref><ref name=\"LautesInterview\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.laut.de/vorlaut/feature/22697/|title=INTERVIEW:\"Der Schlager hat uns einiges versaut\"|accessdate=17 August 2009|publisher=Laut.de|language=German}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe band was founded in 2005.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rockbuster.de/band_info.php?cat=3&id=716 |title=Auletta Band-info |accessdate=17 August 2009 |publisher=Rockbuster Contest |language=German |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719075639/http://www.rockbuster.de/band_info.php?cat=3&id=716 |archivedate=19 July 2011 }}</ref> In 2007 the band got their break by performing at the [[Emergenza]] European festival<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.web-ritz.com/a/band/auletta |title=Auletta |publisher=Web-ritz |accessdate=17 August 2009 |language=German }}{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and later that same year they won the 'Rockbuster' competition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rockbuster.de/article.php?cat=1&id=241 |title=AULETTA gewinnen ROCKBUSTER 2007, THE CURLS und KILLING GLANCE sind ebenfalls Preistr\u00e4ger! |date=4 November 2007 |accessdate=17 August 2009 |publisher=Rockbuster contest |language=German |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719080434/http://www.rockbuster.de/article.php?cat=1&id=241 |archivedate=19 July 2011 }}</ref>  The following year, they appeared with [[Art Brut]] and [[Kilians]].<ref name=\"Ringrocker\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ringrocker.com/lineup.php?op=showrrtalents&menu=82&luid=1013|title=Auletta show review|year=2008|accessdate=20 August 2009|publisher=Ringrocker|language=German}}</ref> At the end of 2008, Auletta signed a record deal with [[EMI]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.regioactive.de/story/7614/mainz_wie_es_singt_und_lacht_auletta_unterschreiben_bei_emi.html|title=Mainz wie es singt und lacht: Auletta unterschreiben bei EMI|date=28 November 2008|accessdate=17 August 2009|publisher=Regioactive|language=German}}</ref> On 26 June 2009, the band released their first album \"P\u00f6belei & Poesie\" (literally translated as ''Vulgarity and poetry''). \"Meine Stadt\" (''My Town''), one of the songs on the album, was included in [[EA Sports]] video game, ''[[FIFA 10]]''. On 1 October 2010, the band represented [[Rheinland-Pfalz]] at the [[Bundesvision Song Contest]] 2010 and finished 14th place out of 16 performing \"Sommerdiebe\" (''Summer thieves'').<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tvtotal.prosieben.de/tvtotal/specials/bundesvision2010/06854.html |title=Bundesvision Song Contest results |publisher=TV Total |accessdate=24 December 2010 |language=German |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101113120217/http://tvtotal.prosieben.de/tvtotal/specials/bundesvision2010/06854.html |archivedate=13 November 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Release date || Type of release || Title || Relevant German chart peak\n|-\n| 2007 || [[Extended Play|EP]] || ''Heimatmelodien'' || &ndash;\n|-\n| 8 May 2009 || Single || ''Meine Stadt'' || &ndash;\n|-\n| 19 June 2009 || Single || ''Ein Engel Kein K\u00f6nig'' || &ndash;\n|-\n| 26 June 2009 || Album || ''P\u00f6belei & Poesie'' ||  93\n|-\n| 8 February 2010 || Single || ''P\u00f6belei & Poesie'' || &ndash;\n|-\n| 24 September 2010 || Single || ''Sommerdiebe'' || 80\n|-\n| 12 August 2011 || Album || ''Make Love Work'' || 36\n|-\n| 2011 || Single || ''Make Love Work'' || 54\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website}} (in German)\n* [http://www.laut.de/wortlaut/artists/a/auletta/index.htm Auletta] profile on Laut.de (in German)\n* {{MusicBrainz artist|id=932937ab-f248-478c-906e-05e23aea3562|name=Auletta}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:German indie rock groups]]\n[[Category:Participants in the Bundesvision Song Contest]]\n[[Category:EMI Group artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n|name             = Auletta\n|image            = \n|caption          = \n| background  = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = [[Mainz]], [[Germany]]\n|genre            = [[Indie Rock]], [[Alternative rock|Alternative]]\n| years_active    = {{Start date|2005}}&ndash; present\n| label           = EMI Germany\n| website             = {{URL|auletta.de}} \n| current_members    = Alexander Zwick <br> Martin Kloos <br> Johannes Juschzak <br> Daniel Juschzak \n| past_members    =\n}}\n\n'''Auletta''' is an [[Indie-Rock]] band from [[Mainz]], [[Germany]]. The band named itself after the town [[Auletta]] in Italy, where they went on holiday in 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.laut.de/wortlaut/artists/a/auletta/biographie/index.htm|title=Auletta Biography|accessdate=17 August 2009|publisher=Laut.de|language=German}}</ref><ref name=\"LautesInterview\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.laut.de/vorlaut/feature/22697/|title=INTERVIEW:\"Der Schlager hat uns einiges versaut\"|accessdate=17 August 2009|publisher=Laut.de|language=German}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n\nThe band was founded in 2005.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rockbuster.de/band_info.php?cat=3&id=716 |title=Auletta Band-info |accessdate=17 August 2009 |publisher=Rockbuster Contest |language=German |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719075639/http://www.rockbuster.de/band_info.php?cat=3&id=716 |archivedate=19 July 2011 }}</ref> In 2007 the band got their break by performing at the [[Emergenza]] European festival<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.web-ritz.com/a/band/auletta |title=Auletta |publisher=Web-ritz |accessdate=17 August 2009 |language=German }}{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and later that same year they won the 'Rockbuster' competition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rockbuster.de/article.php?cat=1&id=241 |title=AULETTA gewinnen ROCKBUSTER 2007, THE CURLS und KILLING GLANCE sind ebenfalls Preistr\u00e4ger! |date=4 November 2007 |accessdate=17 August 2009 |publisher=Rockbuster contest |language=German |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719080434/http://www.rockbuster.de/article.php?cat=1&id=241 |archivedate=19 July 2011 }}</ref>  The following year, they appeared with [[Art Brut]] and [[Kilians]].<ref name=\"Ringrocker\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ringrocker.com/lineup.php?op=showrrtalents&menu=82&luid=1013|title=Auletta show review|year=2008|accessdate=20 August 2009|publisher=Ringrocker|language=German}}</ref> At the end of 2008, Auletta signed a record deal with [[EMI]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.regioactive.de/story/7614/mainz_wie_es_singt_und_lacht_auletta_unterschreiben_bei_emi.html|title=Mainz wie es singt und lacht: Auletta unterschreiben bei EMI|date=28 November 2008|accessdate=17 August 2009|publisher=Regioactive|language=German}}</ref> On 26 June 2009, the band released their first album \"P\u00f6belei & Poesie\" (literally translated as ''Vulgarity and poetry''). \"Meine Stadt\" (''My Town''), one of the songs on the album, was included in [[EA Sports]] video game, ''[[FIFA 10]]''. On 1 October 2010, the band represented [[Rheinland-Pfalz]] at the [[Bundesvision Song Contest]] 2010 and finished 14th place out of 16 performing \"Sommerdiebe\" (''Summer thieves'').<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tvtotal.prosieben.de/tvtotal/specials/bundesvision2010/06854.html |title=Bundesvision Song Contest results |publisher=TV Total |accessdate=24 December 2010 |language=German |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101113120217/http://tvtotal.prosieben.de/tvtotal/specials/bundesvision2010/06854.html |archivedate=13 November 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Release date || Type of release || Title || Relevant German chart peak\n|-\n| 2007 || [[Extended Play|EP]] || ''Heimatmelodien'' || &ndash;\n|-\n| 8 May 2009 || Single || ''Meine Stadt'' || &ndash;\n|-\n| 19 June 2009 || Single || ''Ein Engel Kein K\u00f6nig'' || &ndash;\n|-\n| 26 June 2009 || Album || ''P\u00f6belei & Poesie'' ||  93\n|-\n| 8 February 2010 || Single || ''P\u00f6belei & Poesie'' || &ndash;\n|-\n| 24 September 2010 || Single || ''Sommerdiebe'' || 80\n|-\n| 12 August 2011 || Album || ''Make Love Work'' || 36\n|-\n| 2011 || Single || ''Make Love Work'' || 54\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website}} (in German)\n* [http://www.laut.de/wortlaut/artists/a/auletta/index.htm Auletta] profile on Laut.de (in German)\n* {{MusicBrainz artist|id=932937ab-f248-478c-906e-05e23aea3562|name=Auletta}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:German indie rock groups]]\n[[Category:Participants in the Bundesvision Song Contest]]\n[[Category:EMI Group artists]]\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix overlinking.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Auletta_(band)"}
